          "noteAutobillingDateEn":"To avoid the fact that your bill will not be able to pay due to no charge incurred because the due date as provided by the service provider has yet to come, you should choose a payment date in the following ways:<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>Option 1: </strong>Find payment period information, which is from the date to the date on the monthly advice of charge or bill and set the recurring payment date after 3 to 5 days from the end of the payment period.<br><strong>Option 2: </strong>View on SMS advising monthly bill payment from service providers and set recurring payment date after 3 to 5 days since the date of receiving the message<br>&nbsp;<br>For example: <br> &emsp; - &nbsp; If you receive an SMS advising to pay the bill on October 8, 2020, you should set the recurring payment date from October 10 to 12, 2020.<br> &emsp; - &nbsp; Alternatively, on the electricity bill showing the payment period of October starting from September 7, 2020 to October 6, 2020, you should set the recurring payment date from October 8, 2020 to October 10, 2020."
